{
  "texts": [
    "In order to deal with it, we shall require additional regularity properties on the distribution h(t, w) satisfying (44).As shown in [4, Proposition 1], Eq.",
    "(44) preserves the nonnegativity of any nonnegative initial datum h in ∈ L 1 (I), and hence also its L 1 (I) regularity, since the equation is mass-preserving.",
    "In Proposition 6 we will actually use a more general argument to prove that both the uncontrolled model ( 13) and the controlled one (27) preserve the nonnegativity of any nonnegative initial datum f in ∈ L 1 (R × I) for the whole distribution f (t, A, w).On the other hand, the L q (I) regularity for q > 1 is not always preserved.",
    "Indeed, two situations must be distinguished.",
    "If at least one of the exponents of (47) is negative (which corresponds to opinion polarization, see Subsection 2.3), then the resulting Beta distribution belongs to the space L q (I) for any 1 ≤ q < q *, whereq * = (1 - λ p (ω p + ε) 2 + λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε) σ 2 p + σ 2 ℓ (1 -|µ ℓ |)) -1."
  ]
}